description:
I am getting that error:
Message: CL...: The array extend 1048576 is less than requested 1310721

When sending that SPARUL query:
SPARQL
DELETE FROM <http://freebase.com>
{
  ?s <http://rdf.freebase.com/ns/type.object.type> ?o .
}
WHERE
{
  graph <http://freebase.com> {
    ?s <http://rdf.freebase.com/ns/type.object.type> ?o .
  }
};

Before getting that error, I was getting that other error:
FRVEC: array in for vectored over max vector length 2000000 > 1000000

However, increasing the MaxVectorSize setting to 3M solved that issue.
@HughWilliams you said that the CL... error was due related to a clustering issue in one mailthread a read. However, I am clearly using the Open Source version:
root@SDM:~# virtuoso-t -?
